    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Amorphous, high-temperature, yellowish or transparent thermoplastic developed in 1982 with a molecular weight of Tg = 215C. Characteristics include resistance to ultraviolet and gamma radiation. May be used as reinforcing fiber or as fire-resistant material in electrical components, jets, and automobiles. Resistant to aliphatic hydrocarbons, alcohols, and dilute bases.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>非結晶、具高溫，呈黃色或透明的熱塑性塑膠，以玻璃化溫度(Tg)為215度C的分子量於1982年問世，具有抗紫外線及伽傌射線的特性，可用以強化纖維，也可作為電子零件、噴射機與汽車所需的耐火材料；此外也具備抵抗脂肪族碳氫化合物、酒精及弱鹼之特性。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
